I love this place! I came here for the first time on a Sunday night for dinner and couldn't have been more impressed! Not only was there an excellent Irish folk singer and a banjo player churning out some sweet tunes, but the service, food, and drinks were all excellent as well. While the food is a bit pricey, it's completely worth it and the servings are huge, I couldn't finish my plate, as much as I wanted to! Their Irish mule is great and the house lager is one of the best I've tried. The whiskey selection is next level and I like the cute touch of serving water in a Jameson bottle. It's a pretty big space with loads of seats around the bar and quick, attentive service. It was seriously a treat that I was not expecting on a Sunday night, and some of the best live music I've listened to in a bar in Astoria. The Passage is my new favorite hang out around the 30th Ave area, hands down.

Actual Irish bartender, brogue and all. Delicious coated thick cut fries. Ciders on TAP! TVs. Buy-backs. This is a damn near perfect Irish bar, and you know how I love my Irish bars. I don't throw the word perfect around all willy-nilly.  We came on a slow Monday evening, so I'd like to see what it's like when it's hopping. The space is huge so it could handle it. There really should be more people in here all week long. This place is really great. I'm going to be in the area next week and will make sure to stop by again. Maybe I'll get the Cider flight the next time.

Fun and super LOUD!!! Wish they'd turn down the speakers to 10/10 while customers are dining. We shouted over our meals! 12/10 volume!! Food was really good ... Really good whiskey choices... a whole wall menu of whiskey! Enjoyed a few tastes. Harp on draft was super bland ... skip that!! Nice Irish signage,  though it was hard to feel like Ireland was in the house because there was a backroom party of people from Pakistan. Come for a night of Irish music on certain occasions to get the full effect. This place is quite large and filled with young college age students on a typical Friday night. Great neighborhood,  easy parking, loads of choices in this part of Queens. I'll come back to do a pub crawl.
